Probabilistic Methods, Genetic Algorithms, Theory. 

Probabilistic Methods: The paper explores the use of transient Markov chain analysis to model and understand the behavior of finite population GAFOs observed while in transition to steady states. This is a probabilistic method.

Genetic Algorithms: The paper is specifically focused on the properties of genetic algorithms (GAs) being used for function optimization (GAFOs). The paper explores the use of Markov chains to analyze GAFOs.

Theory: The paper discusses the theoretical understanding of the properties of genetic algorithms being used for function optimization. The paper explores the use of transient Markov chain analysis to model and understand the behavior of finite population GAFOs observed while in transition to steady states. The paper provides new insights into the circumstances under which GAFOs will (will not) perform well.
